# React & TypeScript Patterns

## General
- Functional components only, default exports for pages, named exports for shared components
- No semicolons — project uses semicolon-free TypeScript style
- Props typed inline or with a local `interface`, never `FC<Props>` wrapper

## Charts (Recharts)
Every chart follows this pattern:
```tsx
const c = useChartColors()  // always get colors from this hook — never hardcode hex values

<ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">
  <LineChart data={data} margin={{ top: 4, right: 4, bottom: 0, left: -10 }}>
    <CartesianGrid stroke={c.grid} vertical={false} />
    <XAxis dataKey="time" tick={{ fontSize: 10, fontFamily: 'IBM Plex Mono, monospace', fill: c.text }} axisLine={{ stroke: c.grid }} tickLine={false} />
    <YAxis tick={tickStyle} axisLine={false} tickLine={false} />
    <Tooltip content={<ChartTooltip formatter={(v) => `${v}s`} />} />
  </LineChart>
</ResponsiveContainer>
```

Key rules:
- Always wrap charts in `<ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">`
- Always use `<ChartTooltip>` from `../components/charts/ChartTooltip` — never use Recharts default tooltip
- Chart colors come exclusively from `useChartColors()` — tokens: `accent`, `success`, `warning`, `danger`, `purple`, `teal`, `muted`, `grid`, `text`
- `tickStyle` = `{ fontSize: 10, fontFamily: 'IBM Plex Mono, monospace', fill: c.text }`

## New Dashboard Pages
Each page exports a default component named `<Name>Dashboard`, wraps content in:
```tsx
<section className="dashboard">
  <div className="dash-header">...</div>
  {/* KPIs grid, panels, charts */}
</section>
```

## Theme
Access dark mode via `useTheme()` from `../context/ThemeContext` (returns `{ isDark, toggle }`).  
`useChartColors()` already consumes `useTheme` internally — don't duplicate.
